- *** DONE *** don't die if stylesheets can't be loaded. just issue a warning

- *** DONE *** page breaking is still a little messy... block level elements can run off
  the end of the page.  We really need to split the block *at* the current
  child, not the next one.

- *** DONE *** text decoration on longer elements is shifted a little to the left.

- *** DONE *** table column widths borked when width is set from padding?

- *** DONE *** prevent circular loading of CSS pages

- *** DONE - implemented Cellmap instead *** To handle rowspans & to improve
  collapsed border resolution: consider adding 4 'neighbor' arrays to each
  table_cell_frame_decorator: top, right, bottom & left.  These lists point
  to adjacent cells in the appropriate direction.  Rowspanned cells might be
  able to report (actual_height / rowspan) as the height they contribute to
  the row...

